             <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                
                <!-- Text Context -->
                <div class="md:col-span-1 space-y-4">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">The Cost of Consent</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600">
                        In a public blockchain like Ethereum, every interaction (granting or revoking consent) costs "Gas". For a hospital system managing millions of patients, these variable costs are unsustainable.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-gray-600">
                        <strong>Permissioned Systems</strong> (Hyperledger) utilize a fixed infrastructure cost model. While setup is complex, operational transaction costs are near zero, making them <strong>scalable</strong> for frequent data exchanges.
                    </p>
                    <div class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-blue-100">
                        <h5 class="font-bold text-blue-800 text-sm">Research Insight</h5>
                        <p class="text-xs text-blue-700 mt-1">
                            "Gas fees on public chains introduce unpredictable operational expenses. Permissioned chains eliminate this volatility." (Source: Pham 2024, Lacson 2024)
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

